              <Comments>It may be difficult in some languages to speak of ‘false arguments,’ especially if the equivalent of ‘arguments’ is a verb meaning ‘to argue’ or ‘to discuss against someone.‘ One can, however, express the semantic content of ‘false arguments’ (as reflected in λογισμός[b]) by translating as ‘what people say when they argue, but their words are not true’ or ‘they argue with words that are not true.’</Comments>
